description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for new opportunity?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you have excellent communication skills?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you have excellent admin/secretarial skills?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a 12-month secondment/fixed term contract for a project support officer at 0.8wte (30hours) for the North West Paediatric Networks based at Royal Manchester Children’s Hospital. There may be the potential to increase this to 1.0wte (37.5hours) This is to cover the maternity leave of the post holder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Children’s Networks ensure that we all work together to optimise the children’s experience by bringing together patients and their families, charities, health services , commissioners and other stakeholders in the design and consistency of high quality services .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for providing a high quality administrative and secretarial support to these networks, in clinical areas including, Allergy, Infection, Major Trauma, Critical Care and Surgery in children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have a good level of IT skills and be fully competent in Microsoft office packages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to work in team and be able to work without direct supervision. You must be able to prioritise work and act on your own initiative where appropriate, pre-empting problems and working to solve them in an appropriate manner but escalating as and when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rewarding role for those who enjoy a challenge and can demonstrate excellent organisational and communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We actively welcome enquiries about this role, please contact Suzanne Dixon (email: suzanne.dixon@mft.nhs.uk Tel: 0791 7788 380 or &lt;em&gt;michael.wafer@mft.nhs.uk&lt;/em&gt;). The current post holder Louise King and can be contacted via E-mail: louise.little@cmft.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSuzanne DixonJob titleNetwork ManagerEmail addresssuzanne.dixon@mft.nhs.ukTelephone number07917788380Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries are welcomed to the appointing manager (Suzanne Dixon) or the existing post holder (louise.king@mft.nhs.uk) in the first instance.&lt;/p&gt;
